---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { allTenders, openTenders, generatedAt } from '../lib/data.ts';
---
<Layout
  title="Methodology — IndiaTenders"
  description="Exactly where the data comes from, how often it refreshes, what's covered, and — just as important — what isn't."
>
  <article class="prose">
    <h1>Methodology</h1>

    <h2>Source</h2>
    <p>
      Every tender comes from the <strong>Central Public Procurement Portal (CPPP)</strong> —
      <a href="https://eprocure.gov.in/cppp/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">eprocure.gov.in/cppp</a> — the
      Government of India's central listing of active e-procurement tenders. The portal's "latest active
      tenders" list is public; we fetch a bounded number of its newest pages every 6 hours with an
      identifying user-agent and ~1.5s pacing between requests.
    </p>

    <h2>How the index builds</h2>
    <p>
      Each run parses roughly the newest 400 listings and merges them into the accumulated dataset,
      deduplicated by tender ID (republished corrigendum entries update in place). Currently
      <strong>{allTenders.length}</strong> tenders indexed, <strong>{openTenders.length}</strong> open.
      A tender is <strong>OPEN</strong> when its bid-closing timestamp (IST) is in the future — that's a
      derivation, not an editorial judgement. Closed tenders are kept ~60 days, then dropped.
    </p>

    <h2>Data-quality gates</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Rows that don't parse cleanly are skipped and counted — never guessed at.</li>
      <li>A run that parses zero tenders (markup change) refuses to publish and fails red.</li>
      <li>A run that would shrink the dataset below 70% of its previous size refuses to overwrite it.</li>
      <li>Categories are inferred from title keywords by tested rules — the detail page says so. CPPP sometimes publishes only a reference code as the title (e.g. <code>69/EE(E)/LKO/2026-27</code>); with no describable words, those are honestly left as "Other" rather than guessed.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>What this index does NOT cover (yet)</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>GeM</strong> (Government e-Marketplace) bids.</li>
      <li><strong>State portals</strong> not mirrored to CPPP (e.g. many mahatenders.gov.in listings).</li>
      <li>Tender <strong>values/EMD</strong> — the CPPP list page doesn't publish them; the official detail page does.</li>
      <li>Anything deeper than CPPP publishes in its list: always read the official tender document before bidding.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Coverage grows run by run. Last refresh: <strong>{new Date(generatedAt).toUTCString()}</strong>.
      The scraper, parser, and its tests are open —
      <a href="https://github.com/Nandanhegde1/india-tenders" rel="noopener" target="_blank">read the code</a>.
    </p>
  </article>
</Layout>
